<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1436,152,711]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,326,191,217]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Wing maculated; crossvein m-m close to origin of M 
<number box="[952,960,208,222]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" value="2.0">2</number>
; apex of maxillary palpus curved; gonostylus swollen, rounded distally; ejaculatory apodeme long, surpassing base of gonocoxite; gonocoxal apodeme short.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="29" lastPageNumber="30" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1436,152,711]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,269,314,340]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Male.</emphasis>
Body length, 9.0– 
<quantity box="[488,582,314,340]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.5" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" unit="mm" value="9.5">9.5 mm</quantity>
. Wing length, 6.0– 
<quantity box="[804,897,314,340]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.6" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" unit="mm" value="6.6">6.6 mm</quantity>
. General color brown. Brownish yellow eyes, facets homogenous, ocellar tubercle dark brown, ocelli yellow. Gena, clypeus and antenna brown, clypeus bare. Scape bare, half the length of pedicel; pedicel cubic; first flagellomere suboval, shorter than pedicel (
<figureCitation box="[159,278,434,460]" captionStart="FIGURES 84 – 87" captionStartId="27.[151,269,1929,1953]" captionTargetBox="[245,1343,774,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[245,1438,774,1901]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 84 – 87. Chrysopilus caligatus sp. n., male holotype: 84 — Wing, 85 — Antenna, 86 — Maxillary palpus, female paratype: 87 — Spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177250/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
Figure 
<number box="[245,278,434,460]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" value="85.0">85</number>
</figureCitation>
). Maxillary palpus long, slender, curved apically (
<figureCitation box="[872,992,434,460]" captionStart="FIGURES 84 – 87" captionStartId="27.[151,269,1929,1953]" captionTargetBox="[245,1343,774,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[245,1438,774,1901]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 84 – 87. Chrysopilus caligatus sp. n., male holotype: 84 — Wing, 85 — Antenna, 86 — Maxillary palpus, female paratype: 87 — Spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177250/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
Figure 
<number box="[959,992,434,460]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" value="86.0">86</number>
</figureCitation>
). Proboscis and labella brownish yellow. Occiput brownish gray, with dark setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1436,152,711]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
Thorax uniformly brown, with golden setae on scutellum, tibiae lighter than femora. Halter bare, stem brownish yellow, knob dark brown. Wing maculated (
<figureCitation box="[787,907,554,580]" captionStart="FIGURES 84 – 87" captionStartId="27.[151,269,1929,1953]" captionTargetBox="[245,1343,774,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[245,1438,774,1901]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 84 – 87. Chrysopilus caligatus sp. n., male holotype: 84 — Wing, 85 — Antenna, 86 — Maxillary palpus, female paratype: 87 — Spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177250/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
Figure 
<number box="[874,907,554,580]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" value="84.0">84</number>
</figureCitation>
); pterostigma pigmented, long; surroundings of crossveins pigmented; R 
<number box="[476,484,611,625]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number box="[493,500,611,625]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" value="3.0">3</number>
reaching C, far from R 
<number box="[782,790,611,625]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" value="1.0">1</number>
, without distal sinuosity; R 
<number box="[1120,1128,611,625]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" value="4.0">4</number>
forking with almost right angle, slightly curved distally toward anterior margin, without short appendage; CuA 
<number box="[1154,1162,653,667]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" value="2.0">2</number>
and A 
<number box="[1241,1249,653,667]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" value="1.0">1</number>
fusing far from margin; crossvein m-m close to origin of M 
<number box="[662,670,697,711]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" value="2.0">2</number>
.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177250/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" targetBox="[245,1343,774,1901]" targetPageId="27">
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1436,1929,1987]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,351,1929,1953]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">FIGURES 84–87.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[360,596,1929,1952]" class="Insecta" family="Rhagionidae" genus="Chrysopilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caligatus" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[360,596,1929,1952]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Chrysopilus caligatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[604,666,1929,1953]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[604,666,1929,1953]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">sp. n.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, male holotype: 84 — Wing, 85 — Antenna, 86 — Maxillary palpus, female paratype: 87 — Spermatheca.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177251/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" targetBox="[182,1404,194,1727]" targetPageId="28">
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1436,1752,1810]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,350,1752,1776]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">FIGURES 88–92.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[357,591,1753,1776]" class="Insecta" family="Rhagionidae" genus="Chrysopilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caligatus" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[357,591,1753,1776]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Chrysopilus caligatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[598,658,1752,1776]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[598,658,1752,1776]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, male holotype: 88 — Terminalia, dorsal view, 89 — Terminalia, dorsal view, female paratype: 90 — Terminalia, ventral view, 91 — Sternite VIII, ventral view, 92 — Genital fork (S IX).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,1862,2008]" lastBlockId="29.[151,1437,152,498]" lastPageId="29" lastPageNumber="30" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
Abdomen homogeneously dark brown, tergite of first segment with silvery setae, forming an iridescent band. Gonocoxite brown; gonostylus brownish yellow, swollen, slightly rounded distally, with long setae; aedeagus and ejaculatory apodemes long, the later exceeding base of terminalia; gonocoxal apodeme short; lateral ejaculatory process slender, parallel to ejaculatory apodeme (
<figureCitation box="[942,1060,1982,2008]" captionStart="FIGURES 88 – 92" captionStartId="28.[151,269,1752,1776]" captionTargetBox="[182,1404,194,1727]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[182,1404,194,1728]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURES 88 – 92. Chrysopilus caligatus sp. n., male holotype: 88 — Terminalia, dorsal view, 89 — Terminalia, dorsal view, female paratype: 90 — Terminalia, ventral view, 91 — Sternite VIII, ventral view, 92 — Genital fork (S IX)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177251/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
Figure 
<number box="[1027,1060,1982,2008]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" value="88.0">88</number>
</figureCitation>
); meso-anterior incision of tergite IX deep (
<figureCitation box="[296,415,152,178]" captionStart="FIGURES 88 – 92" captionStartId="28.[151,269,1752,1776]" captionTargetBox="[182,1404,194,1727]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[182,1404,194,1728]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURES 88 – 92. Chrysopilus caligatus sp. n., male holotype: 88 — Terminalia, dorsal view, 89 — Terminalia, dorsal view, female paratype: 90 — Terminalia, ventral view, 91 — Sternite VIII, ventral view, 92 — Genital fork (S IX)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177251/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
Figure 
<number box="[382,415,152,178]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" value="89.0">89</number>
</figureCitation>
); cercus brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1437,152,498]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,295,191,217]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Female.</emphasis>
Body length, 9.0–10.0 mm. Wing length, 6.0– 
<quantity box="[868,964,192,218]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" unit="mm" value="6.5">6.5 mm</quantity>
. Thorax and abdomen similar to male. Anterior margin of sternite VIII rounded, hypogynial valves with at least six long setae (
<figureCitation box="[1212,1332,232,258]" captionStart="FIGURES 88 – 92" captionStartId="28.[151,269,1752,1776]" captionTargetBox="[182,1404,194,1727]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[182,1404,194,1728]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURES 88 – 92. Chrysopilus caligatus sp. n., male holotype: 88 — Terminalia, dorsal view, 89 — Terminalia, dorsal view, female paratype: 90 — Terminalia, ventral view, 91 — Sternite VIII, ventral view, 92 — Genital fork (S IX)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177251/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
Figure 
<number box="[1300,1332,232,258]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" value="91.0">91</number>
</figureCitation>
); genital fork with anterior end strongly acuminate, distal apodemes wide (
<figureCitation box="[945,1067,272,298]" captionStart="FIGURES 88 – 92" captionStartId="28.[151,269,1752,1776]" captionTargetBox="[182,1404,194,1727]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[182,1404,194,1728]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURES 88 – 92. Chrysopilus caligatus sp. n., male holotype: 88 — Terminalia, dorsal view, 89 — Terminalia, dorsal view, female paratype: 90 — Terminalia, ventral view, 91 — Sternite VIII, ventral view, 92 — Genital fork (S IX)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177251/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
Figure 
<number box="[1034,1067,272,298]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" value="92.0">92</number>
</figureCitation>
); cercus two-segmented, distal segment elongated (
<figureCitation box="[392,514,312,338]" captionStart="FIGURES 88 – 92" captionStartId="28.[151,269,1752,1776]" captionTargetBox="[182,1404,194,1727]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[182,1404,194,1728]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURES 88 – 92. Chrysopilus caligatus sp. n., male holotype: 88 — Terminalia, dorsal view, 89 — Terminalia, dorsal view, female paratype: 90 — Terminalia, ventral view, 91 — Sternite VIII, ventral view, 92 — Genital fork (S IX)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177251/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
Figure 
<number box="[481,514,312,338]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" value="90.0">90</number>
</figureCitation>
); common spermathecal ducts short, spermathecal ducts long; spermathecae slender, oblong (
<figureCitation box="[345,464,352,378]" captionStart="FIGURES 84 – 87" captionStartId="27.[151,269,1929,1953]" captionTargetBox="[245,1343,774,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[245,1438,774,1901]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 84 – 87. Chrysopilus caligatus sp. n., male holotype: 84 — Wing, 85 — Antenna, 86 — Maxillary palpus, female paratype: 87 — Spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177250/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
Figure 
<number box="[431,464,352,378]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" value="87.0">87</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[197,951,391,418]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1437,152,498]" box="[197,951,391,418]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,357,391,417]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Distribution.</emphasis>
This species is known only from the type-locality.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="30" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1437,152,498]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,338,431,457]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species name comes from the Latin word 
<taxonomicName box="[881,989,432,457]" class="Insecta" family="Rhagionidae" genus="Chrysopilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caligatus">
<emphasis box="[881,989,432,457]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">caligatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, common soldier, as a reference to the wing brown stripes, resembling a military dress.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
